  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Making Oil Work for Poor People in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The emergence of the oil sector in western Uganda has raised hopes of significant local economic upturn and new job creation. However experience in areas such as the Niger Delta shows how in the long-term oil extraction can severely undermine the livelihoods of resident communities, especially the poorest groups. This project aims to build the capacity of micro and small enterprises and local workers to compete for new business opportunities and jobs. The project will also raise awareness among oil companies and the government of the need for purchasing practices which provide incentives for contractors to engage local micro and small enterprises and workers.</narrative>
  </description>
